### 1.2 Experiencing Original Open-Source Components
You can experience the following original open-source components in the MindSpore community:
- [[MindSpore Lite](https://www.mindspore.cn/lite/en)]: ultra-fast, smart, and simplified device-side AI engine
- [[MindInsight](https://www.mindspore.cn/mindinsight/docs/en/master/index.html)]: visualized debugging and optimization tool of MindSpore
- [[MindSpore Hub](https://www.mindspore.cn/hub/docs/en/master/index.html)]: pre-trained model application tool of the MindSpore ecosystem
- [[MindArmour](https://www.mindspore.cn/mindarmour/docs/en/master/index.html)]: protecting MindSpore security and privacy
- [[MindSpore Federated](https://www.mindspore.cn/federated/docs/en/master/index.html)]: open-source federated learning framework
- [[MindSpore Serving](https://www.mindspore.cn/serving/docs/en/master/index.html)]: helping MindSpore developers efficiently deploy online inference services in the production environment
- [[MindSpore Probability](https://www.mindspore.cn/probability/docs/en/master/index.html)]: providing a comprehensive probability learning library for users to build probability models and apply Bayesian inference
- [[MindQuantum](https://www.mindspore.cn/mindquantum/docs/en/master/index.html)]: quantum machine learning library developed based on MindSpore and HiQ, supporting training and inference of multiple quantum neural networks
- [[MindScience](https://www.mindspore.cn/mindscience/docs/en/master/index.html)]: scientific computing industry suite based on MindSpore converged architecture
- [[MindSpore XAI](https://www.mindspore.cn/xai/docs/en/master/index.html)]: MindSpore-based explainable AI toolkit
- [[MindSpore Reinforcement](https://www.mindspore.cn/xai/docs/en/master/index.html)]: open-source reinforcement learning framework.
- [[MindSpore Graph Learning](https://www.mindspore.cn/graphlearning/docs/en/master/index.html)]:efficient and easy-to-use graph learning framework
## 2. Signing CLA
Before contributing to the MindSpore community, you need to sign the open-source contributor license agreement (CLA) to ensure that the contributions (mainly source code) provided by developers are authorized to the community. In this way, the MindSpore community can accept the contributions. To avoid copyright disputes between the two parties, we contribute code to the open-source community instead of a certain company.

Click [[CLA](https://clasign.osinfra.cn/sign/Z2l0ZWUlMkZtaW5kc3BvcmU=)], and choose to sign the individual CLA, employee CLA, or corporation CLA based on your identity.

Individual CLA: To join the community as an individual, please sign the individual CLA.

Corporation CLA: To join the community as a corporation, please sign the corporation CLA.

Employee CLA: To join the community as an enterprise employee, please sign the employee CLA.

## 3. Joining the MindSpore Community
### 3.1 Participating in Community Activities
You can learn about and participate in community activities in the following ways:
- [[Calendar](https://www.mindspore.cn/community/activities/en)]: such as MSG, MindCon, and offline conferences

### 3.2 Finding Your SIG/Working Groups

#### 1. Find SIGs.

SIG is short for Special Interest Group. The MindSpore community is organized based on different SIGs, facilitating the management and improvement of working processes. So, the first thing you need to do after joining the community is to find an SIG that you are interested in. SIGs are open to everyone.
Currently, the MindSpore community has more than 15 SIGs. You can find SIGs in the [[MindSpore SIG List](https://gitee.com/mindspore/community/tree/master/sigs)].

#### 2. Create an SIG.
If you are interest in a subject and voluntarily head a group, you can create a SIG by submitting a proposal to the steering committee. The chairman will make discussions and help generate proposals and decisions.
#### 3. Find working groups.
In addition to SIGs, the MindSpore community is organized based on different working groups so you can better participate in the community. Find working groups that you are interested in. Anybody is welcomed. You can find working groups in the [[Working Groups List](https://gitee.com/mindspore/community/tree/master/working-groups)].

### 3.3 Contributing to the Community
After signing a [[CLA](https://clasign.osinfra.cn/sign/Z2l0ZWUlMkZtaW5kc3BvcmU=)] and joining SIGs/Working Groups, you can start your community contribution. There are many ways to contribute to the community, and each contribution is welcomed and valued by the community.

Note: You must comply with the [[MindSpore Community Code of Conduct](https://gitee.com/mindspore/community/blob/master/code-of-conduct_en.md)].

#### 1. Commit or handle an issue.
Sending detailed reports when encountering problems is a good way to contribute to projects. MindSpore welcomes your suggestions, comments, and questions for our projects.
- Find the issue list.

On the Gitee home page of a project that you are interested in (for example, [[MindSpore repository](https://gitee.com/mindspore/mindspore)]), click Issues to view the issue list.
- Commit an issue.

If you want to report bugs, submit requirements, or provide comments or suggestions for the MindSpore community, commit issues in the corresponding repository of the MindSpore community.
For details about the precautions for committing an issue, see [[Report issues](https://gitee.com/mindspore/mindspore/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#report-issues)].
You can also attach the issue link to your email and send it to everyone through the [[mailing list](https://gitee.com/mindspore/community/blob/master/communication/mailing-list-guidelines_en.md)].
- Discuss an issue.

Participants communicate and discuss on each issue page. You can leave your opinions in the comment box.
- Handle an issue.

If you want to process one of the issues, you can assign it to yourself by claiming it in the comments below.

#### 2. Contribute code.
- Prepare an environment suitable for MindSpore development. For details, see [[Install](https://www.mindspore.cn/install/en)].
- Understand the development precautions of the project.
The coding language, development environment, and coding conventions used by projects may vary in each project. If you want to know and participate in the code contribution, find the contributor guide provided by the project for developers. This guide is generally provided as the \`CONTRIBUTING.md\` file on the home page of the code repository, alternatively, you can find it in the \`README.md\` file of the project.
- Download code and pull a branch.
To contribute code, you need to know how to download code from Gitee and integrate code through PR. For details, see [[Gitee User Guide](https://gitee.com/help)].
- Perform modification, build, and local validation.
After the modification is complete on the local branch, build and local verification are performed.
- Commit a pull request (PR).
When you commit a PR, it means that you have started to contribute code to the community. To make your commission easier to accept, please refer to the [[Propose PRs](https://gitee.com/mindspore/mindspore/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#propose-prs)].

#### 3. Contribute documents.
If you are not interested in writing code, you can contribute documents to MindSpore by referring to [[MindSpore-Docs repository](https://gitee.com/mindspore/docs)]. We use MarkdownLint to check the format of Markdown documents. For details about the process and specifications, see [[Contributing Documents](https://gitee.com/mindspore/docs/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING_DOC.md)].

#### 4. Disclose community security issues.
If you find a suspected security issue, please use [[Suspected Security Issue Reporting Template](https://gitee.com/mindspore/community/blob/master/security/template/report-template_en.md)] to provide feedback. For more security information, see [[MindSpore Security](https://www.mindspore.cn/security/en)].

### 3.4 Problem Feedback/Help Seeking

If you have any questions, you can provide feedback or seek help in the following ways:
- Commit issues on the [[Issues](https://gitee.com/mindspore/mindspore/issues)] page of the MindSpore code repository.
- Post a topic titled "Help Seeking" in [[MindSpore Forum](https://forum.huawei.com/enterprise/en/forum-100504.html)] and submit detailed information. Dedicated personnel will solve the issue.

## 4. Growing with the Community
### 4.1 Community Growth Incentive System
Join the growth incentive system of the MindSpore community to become an evangelist or excellent developer. 

### 4.2 Community Governance
The MindSpore community uses an open governance architecture which consists of the MindSpore Community Technical Governance Committee, MindSpore Expert Committee, MindSpore User Committee, and MindSpore Community Manager. For more information, see [[Governance](https://www.mindspore.cn/community/governance/en)].
